            ContentJson = """{"appRoute":"/payables/accounts","startButtonLabel":"Tour Bank Accounts","steps":[{"element":".tab-bar","popover":{"title":"The Accounts Tab","description":"The Accounts and Batches tabs appear only when the CAP-BANK-NACHA capability is enabled and you are an Admin, Manager, or Office Manager. The Accounts tab holds each vendor's ACH bank account. If you don't see these tabs, your install does not originate ACH files from Forge.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":"[data-testid='new-bank-account-btn']","popover":{"title":"New Bank Account","description":"Click here to add a vendor's bank account. You choose the vendor, give the account a nickname, pick Checking or Savings, and enter the 9-digit routing number and the account number. The numbers are encrypted at rest and only ever shown masked.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":"app-data-table","popover":{"title":"The Accounts Table","description":"Each row is one vendor bank account: vendor, nickname, type, the masked routing and account numbers, and a color-coded status chip (Pending Approval, Approved, Prenote Sent, Verified, or Disabled). Because the full numbers are never sent to the browser, you only ever see the masked form here.","side":"top"}},{"element":"app-data-table","popover":{"title":"Approve (Dual Control)","description":"A newly added or changed account starts in Pending Approval. A second user — never the person who entered the numbers — clicks the Approve (check icon) action to clear dual control. The system blocks you from approving an account you changed yourself.","side":"top"}},{"element":"app-data-table","popover":{"title":"Prenote, then Mark Verified","description":"After approval, a zero-dollar prenote entry is sent through the bank (assembled on the Batches tab). The account shows Prenote Sent while the bank's return window runs. Once it passes with no rejection, click Mark verified (verified icon) to make the account payable.","side":"top"}},{"element":"app-data-table","popover":{"title":"Change Numbers & Disable","description":"Change numbers (edit icon) re-enters both numbers and resets the account to Pending Approval — the prior approval no longer counts. Disable (block icon) excludes the account from all batches after a confirmation; re-enabling needs a fresh dual-control approval.","side":"top"}}]}"""
